#DOC id=06--office source=/root/yvon/docs/briefs/lifeos-reference/06--office.md format=toon-doc compressed=2026-06-12T06:40:26.298Z

S|# 06 · Office|> A playful 3D "office space" where the agents live — a visualization of what each agt is doing right now. The owner calls it "a bit of a gimmick, but fun," and a way to make the agt team tangible.
S|Purpose|Turn abstract agt activity into something visual and tangible: a 3D rendered office where each agt has a desk, and you can see whether they're working, in a meeting, or idle, per workspace.
S|Page header|- Title: **The Office**, breadcrumb `Vibe with AI / Office`. // - A tagline: "Your agents, live on the floor — a room per workspace, a desk per agt, and they idle across rooms. Rest aside, never here." // - **Workspace tabs** to switch the floor: **Whole floor**, **Vibe**, **By Design**, **Valhalla** (one room per workspace). // - **Status legend / counters** top-right: **X working**, **X in a meeting**, **X cooling/idle**.
S|The 3D scene|- An isometric/3D rendered open-plan office floor divided into **rooms (one per workspace)**, with **desks (one per agt)**. // - agt avatars are placed at desks; their pose/animation reflects state — **at a desk working**, **in a meeting** (gathered around a table), or **idle/cooling**. // - The view is navigable (the floor can be explored; camera can move around the scene). // - Hovering/clicking a desk identifies the agt and what they're doing.
S|Controls (bottom)|- Scene controls and a **"Scroll/zoom to look"** hint. // - A **"Speak to a [room/agt]"** action to jump into talking with an agt from the floor.
S|Design intent|Primarily a tangibility/delight feature, explicitly flagged as a gimmick that will be **built out and improved over time** into a richer 3D world where the agents "live." It complements the data-dense Agents/Org Chart pages with an at-a-glance, human-feeling status view.